🛠 Step-by-Step Guide to Installing Prometheus on EC2
1. Launch an EC2 Instance
AMI: Use Amazon Linux 2 or Ubuntu 22.04 for compatibility.

Instance type: t2.micro (for testing) or larger for production.

Security group: Allow inbound traffic on port 9090 (Prometheus default) and 22 (SSH).

2. Connect to Your Instance
bash
ssh -i your-key.pem ec2-user@<EC2-Public-IP>

3. Install Dependencies
Update packages and install wget/tar:

bash
sudo yum update -y   # Amazon Linux
sudo yum install wget tar -y

4. Download Prometheus
bash
wget https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus/releases/download/v2.52.0/prometheus-2.52.0.linux-amd64.tar.gz
tar xvf prometheus-2.52.0.linux-amd64.tar.gz
cd prometheus-2.52.0.linux-amd64

5. Configure Prometheus
Create or edit prometheus.yml:

yaml
global:
  scrape_interval: 15s

scrape_configs:
  - job_name: 'prometheus'
    static_configs:
      - targets: ['localhost:9090']

6. Run Prometheus
bash
./prometheus --config.file=prometheus.yml
Access via browser: http://<EC2-Public-IP>:9090

7. (Optional) Run as a Service
Create a systemd service file /etc/systemd/system/prometheus.service:

ini
[Unit]
Description=Prometheus
After=network.target

[Service]
ExecStart=/home/ec2-user/prometheus-2.52.0.linux-amd64/prometheus --config.file=/home/ec2-user/prometheus-2.52.0.linux-amd64/prometheus.yml
Restart=always

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
Enable and start:

8. Set Permissions
chmod +x /home/prometheus/prometheus-2.52.0.linux-amd64/prometheus
chown -R prometheus:prometheus /home/prometheus/prometheus-2.52.0.linux-amd64

bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable prometheus
sudo systemctl start prometheus
